ASPECTS\
- \'91aspect\'92 is the logic you want spring to execute when you call specific methods\
- \'91advice\'92 is the timing of the logic execution, befor/after/instead of the method call\
- \'91pointcut\'92 is the method/s spring needs to intercept\
- \'91target object\'92 is the bean that declares the pointcut\
- \'91joinpoint\'92 is the execution of the pointcut\
- \'91weaving\'92 is spring returning a proxy object instead of a target object, the proxy calls the aspect logic\
\
