===================\
WEB APPS\
===================\
\
Servlet Container		-		translates the HTTP request to a Java object and takes a response from a Java object to return it as an HTTP response to a client\
							translator of HTTP messages for your Java app\
							when the servlet container gets an HTTP request it calls a servlet objects method providing the request as a parameter\
							it has a \'91context\'92 of servlet instances it controls\
\
Servlet				-		a Java object which directly interacts with the servlet container\
							Spring can provide a servlet object, we register this object so a servlet container can call it for any path of the client request\
\
\
NOTE: there has to be some way for the servlet container to know about a servlet, this is done by registering the servlet into the servlet containers configuration (this configuration is done automatically by Spring Boot)\
\
\
Servlets\
\
DispatcherServlet		-		\'93front controller\'94 servlet, receives from servlet container and looks up controller method to call\
							\'93Handler Mapping\'94 is the component that actually finds the controller method, it uses the @RequestMapping\
							DispatcherServlet then calls that method and learns of the view to send back\
							\'93View Resolver\'94 is the component tasked with getting the view content\
							DispatcherServlet then sends the view back as a response\
